Aim: Write a program which demonstrates the SQL tags
====
Source code:
==========
SQL commands:
============
    create table employee(id int, name varchar2(50),age int, address varchar2(100));
    insert into employee values(1,'imrankhan',20,Chilakaluripet');
    insert into employee values(2,'ayaankhan',18,Chilakaluripet');
   select *from employee;
   commit;
Ecllips:
======
step1:    file->new->DynamicWebProject
      projectName: Functiontag
     Dynamic web module version:3.0
     click on finish
  step2: creating jsp file:
  ============
     Right click on webapp
      create a jsp file
     jsp name: imransql.jsp
    click on finish
step 3:
======
    Download jar file and JSTL file i.e;(jstl+odbc-8) from downloads and right click on WEB-INFO. right click on lib and paste it.
step4:
====
       <% taglib uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/core" prefix="c"%>
      <% taglib uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/Sql" prefix="sql"%>
      <!DOCTYPE html>
       <html>
               <head>
                           <title>Jsp Database</title>
               </head>
               <body>
                         <sql:set DataSource var="database"
                                   driver="Oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleDriver"
                                   url="jdbc:oracle:thin:@localhost:1521:XE"
                                   user="System"
                                   password="tec"
                        />
                       <sql:query var="result" dataSource="${database}">
                              select *from employee
                       </sql:query>
                       <c:forEach var="row" items="${result.rows}">
                            ${row.id} ${row.name} ${row.age} ${row.address}<br>
                       </c:forEach>
               </body>
        </html>
